    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cc-section cc-section--surface">
    <div class="page-width">
      <p class="cc-eyebrow">What we handle</p>
      <h2 class="cc-title">The platform layer you do not need to build <em>yourself</em></h2>
      <div class="cc-handle">
        <article class="cc-support">
          <div class="cc-support__icon"><svg width="30" height="30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5L19 9V15L12 19L5 15V9L12 5Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg></div>
          <div class="cc-support__title">Collector flow</div>
          <ul class="cc-support__list">
            <li>Storefront presentation</li>
            <li>Cart and checkout integration</li>
            <li>NFC activation experience</li>
            <li>Passport and archive logic</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="cc-support">
          <div class="cc-support__icon"><svg width="30" height="30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M7 7H17M7 12H17M7 17H13" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></div>
          <div class="cc-support__title">Operational layer</div>
          <ul class="cc-support__list">
            <li>Collection structure planning</li>
            <li>Edition mapping and upload review</li>
            <li>Archive-ready metadata handling</li>
            <li>Launch readiness support</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="cc-support">
          <div class="cc-support__icon"><svg width="30" height="30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 7H20M6 11H18V18H6V11Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg></div>
          <div class="cc-support__title">Public credibility</div>
          <ul class="cc-support__list">
            <li>Visible reveal archive</li>
            <li>Rarity commitment infrastructure</li>
            <li>Collector-facing trust layer</li>
            <li>Permanent on-platform history</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cc-section page-width">
    <p class="cc-eyebrow">Examples</p>
    <h2 class="cc-title">What a collaboration can <em>look like</em></h2>
    <div class="cc-examples">
      <article class="cc-example">
        <div class="cc-panel-tag">Artist</div>
        <div class="cc-example__title">A 50-piece signed monochrome drop</div>
        <div class="cc-example__desc">One artist, one visual language, one tightly controlled collector release with a public reveal trail.</div>
        <div class="cc-panel-label">Collectors see the archive grow in real time.</div>
      </article>
      <article class="cc-example">
        <div class="cc-panel-tag">Collective</div>
        <div class="cc-example__title">A themed capsule with multiple contributors</div>
        <div class="cc-example__desc">A scene-led release where each IRIS belongs to a wider cultural statement, but all buyers move through one system.</div>
        <div class="cc-panel-label">Strong for events, pop-ups, and shared worlds.</div>
      </article>
      <article class="cc-example">
        <div class="cc-panel-tag">Gallery</div>
        <div class="cc-example__title">An exhibition extension edition</div>
        <div class="cc-example__desc">A collectible program tied to a show, allowing buyers to take part in a reveal mechanic connected to the institution.</div>
        <div class="cc-panel-label">Strong for represented artists and exhibition storytelling.</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cc-section cc-section--surface">
    <div class="page-width">
      <p class="cc-eyebrow">Questions</p>
      <h2 class="cc-title">Before we build a collection <em>together</em></h2>
      <div class="cc-faq" id="CollaborateFaq-{{ section.id }}">
        <div class="cc-faq__item is-open">
          <button class="cc-faq__toggle" type="button">
            <span>
              <span class="cc-faq__toggle-label">FAQ</span><br>
              <span class="cc-faq__question">What kinds of collaborators are you looking for?</span>
            </span>
            <span class="cc-faq__plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="cc-faq__body" style="max-height: 40rem;">
            <div class="cc-faq__body-inner cc-faq__content">Artists, collectives, galleries, and cultural partners with a clear concept and a reason the IRIS format strengthens the release. We care about alignment and quality more than scale alone.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cc-faq__item">
          <button class="cc-faq__toggle" type="button">
            <span>
              <span class="cc-faq__toggle-label">FAQ</span><br>
              <span class="cc-faq__question">Do I need to know the exact edition size before reaching out?</span>
            </span>
            <span class="cc-faq__plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="cc-faq__body"><div class="cc-faq__body-inner cc-faq__content">No. If the concept is strong, we can help shape the right size and structure for the release.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="cc-faq__item">
          <button class="cc-faq__toggle" type="button">
            <span>
              <span class="cc-faq__toggle-label">FAQ</span><br>
              <span class="cc-faq__question">Can I use IRIS for a show, event, or branded capsule?</span>
            </span>
            <span class="cc-faq__plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="cc-faq__body"><div class="cc-faq__body-inner cc-faq__content">Yes. We are open to artist-led and institution-led collaborations, including exhibition programs and culture-forward brand partnerships.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="cc-faq__item">
          <button class="cc-faq__toggle" type="button">
            <span>
              <span class="cc-faq__toggle-label">FAQ</span><br>
              <span class="cc-faq__question">How do we start the conversation?</span>
            </span>
            <span class="cc-faq__plus">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="cc-faq__body"><div class="cc-faq__body-inner cc-faq__content">Use the application form below. A concise concept note, intended scale, and rough timeline are enough for an initial review.</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cc-section cc-cta-final page-width">
    <p class="cc-eyebrow">Collaborate with IRIS NYC</p>
    <h2 class="cc-title">Launch a collection that feels <em>native</em> to IRIS</h2>
    <div class="cc-copy" style="max-width:70rem; margin:2rem auto 0; text-align:center;">If you have a strong artistic direction and want to release through a collector system that already exists, let's talk.</div>
    <div class="cc-btn-row" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a class="cc-btn cc-btn--gold" href="#CollaborateContact-{{ section.id }}">Apply now</a>
      <a class="cc-btn cc-btn--outline" href="/pages/iris-archive">See the archive</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cc-section cc-section--surface page-width" id="CollaborateContact-{{ section.id }}">
    <p class="cc-eyebrow">Application</p>
    <h2 class="cc-title">Tell us about your <em>collection idea</em></h2>
    <div class="cc-copy" style="max-width:68rem; margin-top:2rem;">We review submissions by concept fit, release clarity, and how well the project can live inside the IRIS ecosystem.</div>

    {%- form 'contact', class: 'cc-form', id: 'CollaborateForm-' | append: section.id -%}
      {%- if form.posted_successfully? -%}
        <div class="cc-form__success">Thanks. We received your submission and will review it.</div>
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- if form.errors -%}
        <div class="cc-form__errors">{{ form.errors | default_errors }}</div>
      {%- endif -%}

      <input type="hidden" name="contact[page]" value="Collaborate">
      <div class="cc-form-grid">
        <div class="cc-form-field">
          <label class="cc-form__label" for="CollaborateName-{{ section.id }}">Name</label>
          <input class="cc-form__input" id="CollaborateName-{{ section.id }}" type="text" name="contact[name]" placeholder="Your name" value="{% if form.name %}{{ form.name }}{% endif %}">
        </div>
        <div class="cc-form-field">
          <label class="cc-form__label" for="CollaborateEmail-{{ section.id }}">Email</label>
          <input class="cc-form__input" id="CollaborateEmail-{{ section.id }}" type="email" name="contact[email]" placeholder="you@example.com" value="{% if form.email %}{{ form.email }}{% endif %}">
        </div>
        <div class="cc-form-field">
          <label class="cc-form__label" for="CollaborateType-{{ section.id }}">Collaboration type</label>
          <select class="cc-form__select" id="CollaborateType-{{ section.id }}" name="contact[collaboration_type]">
            <option value="Artist">Artist</option>
            <option value="Collective">Collective</option>
            <option value="Gallery">Gallery / Institution</option>
            <option value="Brand">Brand / Cultural Partner</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="cc-form-field">
          <label class="cc-form__label" for="CollaborateEdition-{{ section.id }}">Planned edition size</label>
          <input class="cc-form__input" id="CollaborateEdition-{{ section.id }}" type="text" name="contact[edition_size]" placeholder="e.g. 50, 120, 250">
        </div>
        <div class="cc-form-field cc-form-field--full">
          <label class="cc-form__label" for="CollaborateIdea-{{ section.id }}">Concept</label>
          <textarea class="cc-form__input" id="CollaborateIdea-{{ section.id }}" name="contact[body]" placeholder="Tell us about the collection idea, timeline, audience, and what you want to build."></textarea>
        </div>
        <div class="cc-form__submit">
          <button class="cc-btn cc-btn--gold" type="submit">Submit application</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    {%- endform -%}
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  (function () {
    var root = document.getElementById('shopify-section-{{ section.id }}');
    if (!root) return;

    var tabButtons = root.querySelectorAll('.cc-tab-button');
    var tabPanels = root.querySelectorAll('.cc-tab-panel');
    tabButtons.forEach(function (button) {
      button.addEventListener('click', function () {
        var target = button.getAttribute('data-target');
        tabButtons.forEach(function (btn) {
          btn.classList.toggle('is-active', btn === button);
          btn.setAttribute('aria-selected', btn === button ? 'true' : 'false');
        });
        tabPanels.forEach(function (panel) {
          panel.classList.toggle('is-active', panel.getAttribute('data-panel') === target);
        });
      });
    });

    var faqItems = root.querySelectorAll('.cc-faq__item');
    faqItems.forEach(function (item) {
      var toggle = item.querySelector('.cc-faq__toggle');
      var body = item.querySelector('.cc-faq__body');
      if (!toggle || !body) return;
      toggle.addEventListener('click', function () {
        var isOpen = item.classList.contains('is-open');
        faqItems.forEach(function (other) {
          other.classList.remove('is-open');
          var otherBody = other.querySelector('.cc-faq__body');
          if (otherBody) otherBody.style.maxHeight = '0px';
        });
        if (!isOpen) {
          item.classList.add('is-open');
          body.style.maxHeight = body.scrollHeight + 'px';
        }
      });
    });
  })();
</script>

